    prop:examine_Between base:Between_June_and_December_2020 ;
    prop:extractedFrom "Between June and December 2020, a total of 109 neonates aged 1 to 21 days, with birth weights ranging from 1795 g to 4200 g, and who met the diagnostic criteria outlined in the \"Expert Consensus on the Diagnosis and Treatment of Neonatal Sepsis\" (2019) were examined in this prospective study, including 35 with sepsis, 36 with localized infections, and 38 without any infections." ;
