    prop:adopt base:20163544759 ;
    prop:extractedFrom "However, when comparing the duration of non-invasive ventilation alone, no significant difference was observed between the CG (8.5 ± 2.8 days) and the BG (9.2 ± 3.0 days, P = 0.215), while the AG had a shorter non-invasive ventilation duration (5.6 ± 3.1 days, P < 0.001) due to its primary reliance on invasive ventilation.",
        "The AG adopted oral endotracheal intubation connected to a servo-controlled ventilator (20163544759, Bird, USA).",
        "The CG had the shortest length of hospital stay (40.5 ± 9.8 days), followed by the BG (42.8 ± 10.7 days), while the AG had the longest (56.3 ± 12.5 days)." ;
