    prop:extractedFrom "In a cohort study of children with severe sepsis or septic shock, Gorgis et al[59] found that early lactate levels (measured within three hours of sepsis onset) were not directly predictive of mortality but correlated significantly with PRISM III score, thus supporting its use as an early severity marker rather than a mortality predictor." ;
