        "Future climate projections indicate global sea-level rise (SLR) will exponentially increase the frequency of coastal flooding, suggesting that 90% of U.S. coastal regions will experience a daily exceedance of present-day 50-year extreme water levels (i.e., 2% annual chance of exceedance) by the end of the twenty-first century4.",
        "On day 10, the US showed a well-defined, homogeneous peripancreatic fluid collection anterior to the pancreatic head, measuring ~20 × 16 mm (TS × AP), with minimal pelvic free fluid (~12 mm in the rectovesical recess) (Figure 7).",
        "This retrospective cohort study evaluated US healthcare claims using Optum’s Clinformatics Data Mart Database.",
        "This retrospective cohort study used US administrative healthcare claims from the Optum Clinformatics Data Mart (CDM) database." ;
