base:sofa_score a type:Biomarker ;
    rdfs:label "sofa score" ;
    prop:allocate_In base:sepsis ;
    prop:associate_with base:sepsis ;
    prop:confirm_as base:30_day ;
    prop:extractedFrom "A shortened sequential organ failure assessment score (SOFA score), known as the quick SOFA score (qSOFA), has replaced the SIRS system of diagnosis.[4]",
        "In this open-label, randomized controlled trial conducted in the acute medical unit of a tertiary academic center, adult patients with sepsis (defined as suspected infection plus a SOFA score increment of ≥2) were allocated to receive either standard sepsis management plus daily oral atorvastatin 20mg or standard management alone for up to 28 days.",
        "ROC curve analysis showed that sphk1, D-lactic acid, I-FABP, APACHEII score, and SOFA score had high predictive value for gastrointestinal injury in patients with sepsis, with area under the curve (AUC) of 0.996, 0.987, 0.976, 0.901, and 0.934 (all P < 0.05).",
        "Regression analysis showed that cTnT, cTnI, p-SOFA score, CRP and PCT levels were significantly associated with the poor prognosis of children with severe sepsis ( cTnI, cTnT, and p-SOFA are closely related to the inflammatory response in children with severe sepsis, and the combination of the three indicators can effectively assess the severity of sepsis.",
        """Severe sepsis is an infectious disease state associated with multiple organ dysfunction syndrome (MODS)[8]
- Septic shock is severe sepsis plus persistently low blood pressure, despite the administration of intravenous fluids.[8]
In 2016, a new consensus was reached to replace screening by systemic inflammatory response syndrome (SIRS) with the sequential organ failure assessment (SOFA score) and the abbreviated version (qSOFA).[4]""",
        "Vancomycin resistance, SOFA score and CCI were confirmed as predictors of 30-day mortality even after removing 102 patients with polymicrobial BSI from the analysis (Table 3B)." ;
    prop:have_with base:sepsis ;
    prop:reach_In base:2016 ;
    prop:replace base:qsofa ;
    prop:sourceUrl "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sepsis"^^xsd:anyURI,
