base:norepinephrine a type:Treatment ;
    rdfs:label "norepinephrine" ;
    prop:administer_for base:4_27_days ;
    prop:extractedFrom "Effect of norepinephrine on ventricular systolic function during septic shock: the ENESySS study To determine whether norepinephrine improves the left ventricle systolic function in early septic shock patients.",
        "If the placement of a central venous catheter is delayed then norepinephrine can be given through a peripheral IV.[59]",
        "In the observation group, hs-CRP, PCT, IL-6, SOFA score, MAP, and norepinephrine dosage showed statistical significance at 24 hours after treatment as compared with before treatment [hs-CRP (mg/L): 125.0 (105.0, 171.2) vs. 280.5 (213.2, 313.8), PCT (μg/L): 51.0 (20.0, 62.8) vs. 71.0 (10.8, 100.0), IL-6 (ng/L): 1 762.2 (300.8, 4 327.5) vs. 4 447.5 (630.4, 5 000.0), SOFA score: 13.0 (12.0, 14.0) vs. 16.0 (15.0, 17.0), MAP (mmHg, 1 mmHg ≈ 0.133 kPa): 79.00±12.87 vs. 65.20±11.70, norepinephrine dosage (μg×kg In the treatment of CRRT, oXiris filter can reduce the short-term mortality of SA-AKI patients, lower inflammatory mediators levels and improve hemodynamics, showing therapeutic advantages over conventional filters.",
        "Norepinephrine is often used as a first-line treatment for hypotensive septic shock because evidence shows that there is a relative deficiency of vasopressin when shock continues for 24 to 48 hours.[77] Norepinephrine raises blood pressure through a vasoconstriction effect, with little effect on stroke volume and heart rate.[5]",
        "Norepinephrine was administered for 4 (2–7) days, and the ICU length of stay was 7 (5–7) days; the ICU mortality was 47%.",
        "Of 11,981 patients with sepsis, 1,827 patients with septic shock receiving norepinephrine were included (108 dobutamine vs. 1,719 no dobutamine; mean age 71.4 ± 13.2 years, 59.4% male).",
        "Our observational study in preload non-responder patients showed that norepinephrine improves LVOT-VTI and other indices of left ventricle systolic function as well as the ventriculoarterial coupling in early septic shock." ;
    prop:give_through base:vasopressor ;
    prop:improve base:septic_shock ;
    prop:improve_in base:septic_shock ;
