base:mechanical_ventilation a type:Treatment ;
    rdfs:label "mechanical ventilation" ;
    prop:determine_from base:icu ;
    prop:extractedFrom "Complication indicesaRespiratory complications [13]:BPD was diagnosed if FiO2 > 21% or mechanical ventilation was required at 36 weeks (corrected gestational age); severity was graded as mild (FiO2 < 30%), moderate (FiO2 30–50%), or severe (FiO2 > 50% or need for mechanical ventilation).Pneumothorax: Cases with intrapleural free air confirmed by chest X-ray, requiring tube thoracostomy or spontaneous resolution.Pulmonary infection was defined by meeting ≥ 2 of the following criteria: temperature > 38℃ or < 36.5℃; leukocyte count > 20 × 10⁹/L or < 5 × 10⁹/L; positive sputum or tracheal-aspirate culture; new infiltrates on chest X-ray.bNeurological",
        "The use of antibiotics, vasopressors, mechanical ventilation, and renal replacement therapy was determined from medication and procedure records spanning the entire ICU stay." ;
    prop:require_at base:36_weeks ;
