base:pct a type:Biomarker ;
    rdfs:label "pct" ;
    prop:assess base:28_day ;
    prop:demonstrate_compared base:crp ;
    prop:emerge_as base:sepsis ;
    prop:extractedFrom "A prospective cohort study [optimizing antibiotic strategies in sepsis (OASIS) study], conducted on 85 children, found that a combination of biomarkers (CRP, serum amyloid A, and PCT) can identify children with SIRS in whom antibiotics might be discontinued at 48 hours[76].",
        "Among the secondary outcomes, biomarkers such as PCT, CRP, TNF-α, and WBC serve as critical indicators for assessing the therapeutic response and systemic inflammation in sepsis [1].",
        "Furthermore, PCT levels correlated with multiple indicators of burn sepsis diagnosis, and elevated PCT may represent a risk factor for acute kidney injury in burn sepsis patients.",
        "In the study, PCT outperformed CRP in diagnostic accuracy of predicting sepsis.[56]",
        "Inflammatory markers (CRP, PCT) remained elevated in oXiris patients through day 5, while hemodynamic stabilization (lactate decline, norepinephrine reduction) was more pronounced.",
        "Logistic regression identified independent risk factors, and receiver operating characteristic curve analysis assessed the predictive value of PCT, Lac, SOFA scores, and the combined model.",
        "Multivariate binary logistic regression analysis of the eight variables identified only PCT (OR 1.168, 95% CI: 1.062~1.284, P=0.001) and hs-CRP (OR 1.01, 95% CI: 1.003~1.017, P=0.004) as independent factors significantly associated with the diagnosis of burn sepsis (Figure 1).",
        """PCT also outperformed other biomarkers such as C-reactive protein.[69]
Gastrointestinal disease
[edit]Evidence shows that an elevated PCT above .5 ng/mL could help diagnose infectious complications of inflammatory bowel disease such as abdominal abscesses, bacterial enterocolitis etc.""",
        "PCT demonstrated superior diagnostic accuracy (sensitivity 89.2%, specificity 83.5%, AUC 0.93) compared to CRP (sensitivity 76.3%, specificity 62.7%, AUC 0.76).",
        "PCT has been extensively studied as a marker associated with infection and sepsis and is effectively utilized in clinical practice.",
        "PCT is emerging as a universal biomarker for both bacterial and non-bacterial sepsis, making it a potential universal marker for sepsis.",
        "PCT not only provides guidance for the diagnosis of burn sepsis but also offers some indication of its severity.31",
        "PCT reduces antibiotic exposure during outbreak of viral meningitis |",
        "PCT was first introduced as a diagnostic marker for sepsis in the early 1990s.",
        "Serum PCT and hs-CRP may serve as valuable biomarkers for the early diagnosis of burn sepsis, with optimal diagnostic thresholds of >1.76 ng/mL and >22.47 mg/L, respectively.",
        "Several related non-burn sepsis studies suggest that the combined use of PCT and CRP can improve the accuracy of sepsis diagnosis, but further research is needed to confirm these findings.49,50",
        "The dynamic changes in these inflammatory biomarkers, particularly PCT, CRP, and LAC, offer valuable prognostic information beyond their baseline levels in predicting 30-day mortality in severe infections.",
        "The inclusion of the NRBC count, combined with CRP and PCT, significantly increases the predictive efficacy of disease severity or progression, particularly indicative of septic shock, highlighting the potential of this combination for early diagnosis and management in pediatric patients.",
        "Therefore, our results are highly reliable, suggesting that PCT holds significant value for the early diagnosis of burn sepsis.",
        "These markers, particularly CRP and PCT, show high sensitivity in distinguishing sepsis from non-infectious conditions.",
        "This followed a 2015 meta analysis that showed that PCT had a sensitivity of 90% and a specificity of 98% in judging viral versus bacterial meningitis.",
        """[47][50] |
Medical uses
[edit]Sepsis
[edit]Measurement of procalcitonin can be used as a marker of severe sepsis caused by bacteria and generally grades well with the degree of sepsis,[51] although levels of procalcitonin in the blood are very low. PCT has the greatest sensitivity (90%) and specificity (91%) for differentiating patients with systemic inflammatory response syndrome (SIRS) from those with sepsis, when compared with IL-2, IL-6, IL-8, CRP and TNF-alpha.[52]""",
        """]
Pediatrics
[edit]In a meta analysis of 17 studies, PCT had a sensitivity of 85% and a specificity of 54% in diagnosing sepsis in neonates and children.""",
        """|
| Postoperative infections | RCT | 0.5-1.0; 75-85% ↓ | ✓✓ | PCT reduces antibiotic exposure without adverse outcomes in the surgical ICU |""",
        "| Pneumonia | RCT | 0.1-0. 5; 80-90% ↓ | ✓✓✓ | PCT reduces antibiotic without adverse outcomes exposure in the hospital |",
        "✓✓✓ | PCT reduces antibiotic exposure without adverse outcomes in the ED |" ;
