base:antibiotic a type:Treatment ;
    rdfs:label "antibiotic" ;
    prop:extractedFrom "Additionally, prior studies have only evaluated the incidence of NEC as one of the clinical outcomes of IEAT [10–12], however, it is yet to be established whether alterations in the gut microbiota resulting from early antibiotic administration can influence the timing of NEC onset, which has been reported to occur around 2 weeks after birth [13, 14].",
        "Although per-hour delays in antibiotic administration showed association with sepsis development (Adjusted Odds Ratio(aOR) (95% CI) 1.071(1.044-1.099); P < 0.001), the primary threshold analysis demonstrated that significant associations with sepsis (aOR (95% CI), 3.468 (2.131-5.623); P < 0.001), in-hospital mortality (aOR 2.487, 95% CI 1.083-5.440; P = 0.026), adverse clinical outcomes, and prolonged LOS emerged only when delays exceeded 12 h.",
        "An alternative to postsurgical antibiotic treatment is using antibiotic-loaded, dissolvable calcium sulfate beads, which are implanted with the medical device.",
        """Antibiotic stewardship
[edit]Procalcitonin guided cessation of antibiotic use reduces duration of antibiotic exposure and lowers mortality in critically ill patients in the Intensive Care Unit.[80]
In adult emergency department patients with respiratory tract illnesses, PCT-guided treatment groups had reduced antibiotic use.[81""",
        "Complete data about antibiotic therapy are reported in Table S1 (available as Supplementary data at JAC Online) in Supplementary material.",
        "Factors that are used to decide de-escalation of antibiotic therapy include the use of biomarkers, such as a decreasing procalcitonin, to monitor response to therapy or clinical progress during treatment.[51]",
        "Fifty-five Escherichia coli bloodstream isolates, 36 multidrug-resistant (MDR) (65.5%) and 19 antibiotic-sensitive (34.5%), underwent phenotypic susceptibility testing using VITEK® 2 and disk diffusion.",
        "However, the number of antibiotic-resistant strains has been increasing year by year due to the limited number of target sites and the widespread utilization of antibiotics.",
        "In case of people having a high risk of being infected with multiple drug resistant organisms such as Pseudomonas aeruginosa, Acinetobacter baumannii, the addition of an antibiotic specific to the organism is recommended.",
        "The term “antibiotic” was introduced by Waksman in 1947 to describe chemical compounds produced by microorganisms capable of inhibiting the growth of other microorganisms [1]." ;
    prop:include base:procalcitonin ;
    prop:increase_due base:antibiotics ;
    prop:influence base:around_2_weeks ;
    prop:introduce_in base:1947 ;
    prop:recommend_In base:pseudomonas_aeruginosa ;
    prop:reduce_In base:pct ;
    prop:report_in base:JAC_Online ;
    prop:show base:sepsis ;
