base:septic_shock a type:Disease ;
    rdfs:label "septic shock" ;
    prop:admit_to base:Policlinico_Universitario_A_Gemelli,
        base:between_December_2016_and_December_2021,
        base:the_Intensive_Care_Department_of_the_Childrens_Hospital ;
    prop:compare_to base:Kyoto ;
    prop:confirm_in base:sepsis ;
    prop:define_as base:sepsis ;
    prop:divide_into base:28_day ;
    prop:extractedFrom "A prospective, single-center study included 54 septic shock patients with central venous catheters placed within 24 h of intensive care unit admission.",
        "A total of 63 patients, comprising 30 males and 33 females, who developed septic shock secondary to pediatric primary peritonitis, were admitted to the Intensive Care Department of the Children's Hospital Affiliated to Xi'an Jiaotong University and the Pediatric Intensive Care Unit of Gansu Provincial Maternity and Child-Care Hospital between December 2016 and December 2021.",
        "A total of 72 septic shock patients were included in our final analysis, excluding those with heart function impairments, including sepsis-induced cardiomyopathy.",
        "Between February 2022 and July 2023, 58 patients with septic shock and hyperinflammation were screened for study inclusion.",
        "Furthermore, when compared with sepsis patients, those experiencing septic shock presented with higher white blood cell counts, creatinine, lactate levels, SOFA and APACHE II scores, along with a greater incidence of AKI and a higher 28-day mortality rate (P<0.01).",
        "It is noted that evidence from septic shock RCTs have in general yielded disappointing results over the years, due in part to the complexity and heterogeneity of this condition [[9], [10], [11]].",
        "Key features of septic shock include profound vasoplegia, refractory hypotension, and multi-organ dysfunction resulting from an overwhelming inflammatory response [1].",
        "Our proteomic analysis identified that 316 and 83 differentially expressed proteins (DEPs) in sepsis and septic shock groups, respectively, each compared to the control group.",
        "Patients from 23 intensive care units in Germany enrolled within 24 hours of the onset of septic shock were followed up for outcome data up to 90 days.",
        "Patients with septic shock who underwent pulse index continuous cardiac output (PiCCO) monitoring within 24 h were included from November 2013 to January 2024.",
        "Patients within the first 4 hours of septic shock were included between March 2022 and April 2025, with last follow-up in July 2025.",
        "Recent international consensus criteria for pediatric sepsis and septic shock defined pediatric sepsis as a Phoenix Sepsis Score (PSS) of ≥ 2 points in children with suspected infection.",
        "Ten adults with sepsis or septic shock admitted to the ICU of \"Fondazione Policlinico Universitario A. Gemelli\" and seven healthy controls were enrolled.",
        "The Randomised Trial of Immunonutrition with L-citrulline in Patients Hospitalised in Intensive Care for Sepsis or Septic Shock (ICITRU) trial (NCT04513288) is investigating the effects of enteral supplementation with the arginine precursor L-citrulline over 5 days in patients with sepsis, with SOFA score as primary outcome.",
        "The patients with septic shock were divided into survival and death groups based on their 28-day survival status.",
        """The risk of septic shock increases at age 60, with those at age 70 having the highest risk of dying from sepsis.[11]
The mortality rate from sepsis, especially if it is not treated rapidly with the needed medications in a hospital, is approximately 40% in adults and 25% in children.[68][69]""",
        "The value of miR-9-5p, a miRNA already listed in the top 10 upregulated differentially expressed miRNAs in patients with sepsis and septic shock[13], has been confirmed in a single-center, prospective, observational cohort study involving 69 sepsis patients, 30 non-sepsis patients, and 35 healthy controls[15].",
        "Wong et al[56] demonstrated that children with septic shock having serum IL-8 levels ≤ 220 pg/mL within 24 hours of admission had a higher likelihood of survival." ;
    prop:follow_for base:up_to_90_days ;
    prop:have base:Zeng ;
    prop:include base:intensive_care_unit,
        base:organ_dysfunction ;
    prop:include_between base:July_2025,
        base:between_March_2022 ;
